Rhodri Lloyd (born (1993-07-22) 22 July 1993 (age18) in Caerphilly) is a Welsh professional rugby league footballer who currently plays for Wigan Warriors in the Super League,[1] and at international level for Wales.[2] He previously played for South Wales Scorpions. Rhodri Lloyd made his dbut for Wales against Italy in 2010 while just 17 years old. In doing so, he became the youngest ever player to win a senior cap for Wales.
